The aeroelastic hysteretic vibration absorber. The well-known Den Hartog viscoelastic VA [132, 165] is effective for vibration control of a mechanical system subject to a harmonic force due to the antiresonance phenomenon which cancels completely the response when the system and the VA are undamped and the frequency of the VA is exactly tuned to the frequency of the system driven to resonance. The antiresonance phenomenon was exploited ﬁrst by Frahm [165]. When the system is damped, there is no exact resonance cancellation while the antiresonance (accompanied by a small non-zero amplitude) is still exhibited provided that the VA frequency is properly tuned to the frequency of the damped system.
